<p>I know a lot of people pluralize &quot;virus&quot; like this, but it really should be &quot;viruses&quot;. &quot;Virii&quot; would be the plural of &quot;virius&quot; which isn't even a word. The Latin word &quot;virus&quot; means &quot;poison&quot;, and is already plural, in the same way that &quot;water&quot; is plural in English. If you really want a Latin plural of &quot;virus&quot;, it would be &quot;viri&quot; (also not a real word).</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
